1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on implementing a parallel BFS algorithm on distributed memory, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - Graph traversal algorithms, including BFS, are commonly studied in the context of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.Distributed - The paper specifically deals with parallelizing BFS on distributed memory, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions that graphs can be used to model real-world scenarios, including communities and their interconnections, which falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper mentions that BFS can be used in communication networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
